values: 一餐；一顿饭；早（或午、晚）餐；膳食；饭菜；粗磨粉；谷物粉末；谷物粗粉

word_mean_info__list.difference: 正餐。指一日中的主餐，可中午吃，也可晚间吃。
泛指一日三餐的任一餐，也可指一餐所吃的东西。

word_group.brief_definition: 膳食计划；就餐计划；营养餐计划
提供生活来源的人；谋生工具

bilingual.source: The evening meal is the most important meal in both countries.
bilingual.target: 晚餐是两国最重要的一餐。
她每天都做一餐丰盛的晚餐。

bilingual.source: They invited us over for a meal.
bilingual.target: 他们邀请我们来他们家吃一餐。

bilingual.source: We enjoyed a meal at the restaurant.
Soups are a great way to start a meal.
bilingual.target: 汤是开始一餐的好方法。

bilingual.source: Breakfast is the most important meal of the day.
bilingual.target: 早饭是一天中最重要的一餐。

bilingual.source: After a busy day, a meal of hot food is satisfying.
bilingual.target: 在忙碌的一天后，一餐热腾腾的饭菜让人感到满足。

bilingual.source: She always eats three meals a day and never skips any meal.
bilingual.target: 她总是按时一日三餐，从不跳过任何一餐。

bilingual.source: We had a picnic in the park and enjoyed a meal of simple lunch.
bilingual.target: 我们在公园里野餐，享受一餐简单的午餐。

bilingual.source: His indecision was evident when he couldn't choose a meal from the menu.
bilingual.target: 当他无法从菜单中选择一餐时，他的犹豫不决显而易见。

list.abstract: meal（英[miːl]，美[miːl]），英语单词，名词，意思为一餐；一顿；粗磨粉。短语搭配有have a meal（吃饭；就餐），例句为“The company already made square metal meal containers.（该公司已生产方形金属餐盒。）” meal名词类近义词有board、feed，不及物动词类近义词有have a dinner、dine。meals是meal的复数形式。

yingyinNormal.en: She enjoyed her meal very much.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她非常喜欢这里的饭菜。

yingyinNormal.en: One meal. That's all I'm asking for. Please?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我只求一顿饭，好吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Perhaps the two of us might share a meal together.
yingyinNormal.zh: 或许咱俩该一起吃个饭。

yingyinNormal.en: This is the definitive Sichuan meal. A fabulously fiery fondue.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是一道经典川菜，绝妙的火锅。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm gonna invite her over. We'll have a nice meal and chat.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要请她过来，我们可以好好吃一顿，然后聊天。

yingyinNormal.en: Have you had a meal with him yet? What if you hate the way he eats?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你跟他吃过饭了吗? 如果你讨厌他的吃相怎么办?

yingyinNormal.en: It's quite a stiff dough because of the rye in there and the whole meal.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在的面团很硬，因为里面有黑麦和全麦面粉。

yingyinNormal.en: At dinner it struck me that we were sharing a meal with a group of strangers.
yingyinNormal.zh: 晚餐时，我突然觉得我们在和一群陌生人共进晚餐。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh and check it out, I made Marcel's favorite dish, banana cake with meal worms.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我做了马修最喜欢吃的菜，香蕉蛋糕，加了虫虫。

yingyinNormal.en: You relaxed at the end of the meal. You open your belt. You release one or two notches.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你吃完后放松地松了松腰带，放了1个或2个孔。

yingyinNormal.en: You know what? I have half a mind to pack up the beautiful meal I made... Dinner is served!
yingyinNormal.zh: 你知道吗？我郑重告诉你，我打算把我做的美味晚餐装好...晚餐上来啦！

yingyinNormal.en: Last night, I experienced something new, an extraordinary meal from a singularly unexpected source.
yingyinNormal.zh: 昨晚我有个全新的体验，一顿奇妙的菜肴来自令人意想不到的出处!

yingyinNormal.en: Okay. We have some friends coming in for a meal and we don't want you guys to embarrass us and overreact.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是这样的，我们有朋友想来店里用餐，我们不想你们让我们丢人，或反应过激。

yingyinNormal.en: We want to buy a really expensive meal. We don't want to eat pork rolls at a stall, even with apple sauce.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们就想吃一顿昂贵的大餐，我们不想去小吃摊吃什么猪肉卷，有苹果酱也不要。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm just gonna run and get the badges, and then we will have our meal. We'll be fine once we've eaten. Yeah.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我马上跑去买票，然后我们就能吃上饭了，吃过东西就好多了。

yingyinNormal.en: You sit down on a Thanksgiving dinner. Your mother-in-law has worked very hard and created a fantastic meal.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你坐在感恩节餐桌上，你的岳母很辛苦地做了一桌的美味佳肴。

yingyinNormal.en: I was just wondering what time you want me to serve your favorite home-cooked meal tonight. Maybe around 8:00?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我就是想问问今晚你想几点吃你最爱的家常菜，8点怎么样？

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, lord, we thank you for this meal and all of your bounty. And we pray that you help Sheldon get back on his rocker.
yingyinNormal.zh: 主啊，感谢您赐予我们晚餐，及您所有的恩赐，我们祈求您帮助谢尔顿重新振作。

yingyinNormal.en: Once you've mastered that, I'm going to reveal how bread can be much more than just a loaf. It can be a meal in itself.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一旦你掌握了，我将告诉你，面包不仅仅是面包，面包本身就是一道大餐。

yingyinNormal.en: They've been away for months and have just flown in from Taiwan. I can't think of anyone better to share this special meal.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们分别了好几个月，刚刚从台湾飞过来，没人比他们更适合与我分享这道菜。

examination_example.sentence: But among student subjects who discussed meat ethics, <highlight>meal</highlight> purchases containing meat decreased from 52 to 45 percent.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但在讨论肉类伦理的学生受试者中，购买含有肉类的膳食的比例从52%下降到45%。

examination_example.sentence: It is far better to spend money on experiences, like interesting trips, unique <highlight>meals</highlight> or even going to the cinema.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 把钱花在体验上要好得多，比如有趣的旅行，独特的餐食，甚至是去看电影。

examination_example.sentence: She associated it with abundant Thanksgiving <highlight>meals</highlight> that she claimed had "a deep moral influence."
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她将其与丰富的感恩节大餐联系在一起，她声称这对感恩节有“深远的道德影响”。

examination_example.sentence: When people were encouraged to take at least three photos while they ate lunch, they were more immersed in their <highlight>meals</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当人们被鼓励在吃午饭时至少拍三张照片时，他们更能沉浸在饭菜中。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>meals</highlight> are not particularly appetising, or even safe.

examination_example.sentence: Around the beginning of the nineteen fifties, some school kids started to use metal <highlight>meal</highlight> containers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大约在二十世纪五十年代初，一些学生开始使用金属餐盒。

examination_example.sentence: As schools have changed in the past century, the midday <highlight>meal</highlight> container has evolved right along with them.

examination_example.sentence: The durability of metal <highlight>meal</highlight> containers benefited consumers.

examination_example.sentence: It is always crowded with customers at <highlight>meal</highlight> times.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 吃饭的时候总是挤满了顾客。

examination_example.sentence: People who eat slowly tend to consume about 70 fewer calories per <highlight>meal</highlight> than those who rush through their meals.

examination_example.sentence: In one study, people who ate <highlight>meals</highlight> in a blue room consumed 33 percent less than those in a yellow or red room.
